  "prompt": "[SPOLIERS]Are all the Children of the Forest dead?",
  "response": "In *A Song of Ice and Fire* and its TV adaptation *Game of Thrones*, the Children of the Forest are not entirely extinct, but their numbers have drastically dwindled. By the time of the events in the series, they are very rare and largely secluded, living in remote areas like the caves beyond the Wall.\n\nIn the books, there are hints that some Children of the Forest still exist, particularly in association with the Three-Eyed Raven. In the show, it is revealed that the Children created the White Walkers thousands of years ago as a weapon against humans but lost control of them. The last known group of Children in the show is wiped out during the conflict with the Night King and his army, but it's unclear if others might still exist elsewhere.\n\nSo, while heavily diminished and seemingly on the brink of extinction, it's possible that a few Children of the Forest still survive, especially in the books.",
